title: "Colombia 2026 Hybrid ABM–LLM Runoff Simulation"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Molina"
    given-names: "Katherin"
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-06-22"
license: MIT
abstract: >-
  A twenty-day synthetic agent-based and LLM-assisted computational experiment
  studying information ingestion, adaptive trust, semantic reframing, social
  transmission, emergence, and simulated voting-state deliberation in a
  Colombian presidential-runoff scenario.
keywords:
  - agent-based modelling
  - multi-agent systems
  - computational social science
  - information dynamics
  - large language models
  - electoral simulation
  - Colombia
